<h1>Fernando Gros</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://fernandogros.com/now">fernandogros.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Tokyo

Japan
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Photographer
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I create windows into the way people live around the world.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I’m fascinated by the way people adapt to life in different places, by the culture and traditions, art and music they create to express themselves and give meaning to their lives.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Snark and cynicism feel old today in the way “we’ve always done it this way” attitudes felt old when I was growing up.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Shop Class as Soulcraft: An Inquiry Into the Value of Work by Matthew Crawford
</p>

